# {{.Type}} ({{.Name}})

{{ .Description | trimspace }}

The support contact information is displayed to users in the **Help and Support** page within Business Central. This allows partners and administrators to provide customized support contact details for their Business Central environments.

## Important Notes

~> **Warning:** Deleting this resource will only remove it from Terraform state. The Business Central Admin Center API does not provide a DELETE endpoint for support contacts, so the contact information will remain configured on the environment. To clear the support contact, you must manually update it in the Business Central Admin Center or set it to different values.

-> **Note:** The support contact is environment-specific. Each environment can have its own support contact configuration.

-> **Note:** Use the `aad_tenant_id` argument to specify which Azure AD tenant this resource belongs to. If omitted, it defaults to the provider's configured `tenant_id`.

## Example Usage

### Basic Support Contact

{{tffile "examples/resources/bc_admin_center_environment_support_contact/resource.tf"}}

### Partner Support Portal

```terraform
resource "bcadmincenter_environment_support_contact" "partner" {
  application_family = "BusinessCentral"
  environment_name   = "Production"
  
  name  = "Contoso Partner Support"
  email = "bc-support@contoso.com"
  url   = "https://support.contoso.com/business-central"
}
```

### Multiple Environment Support

```terraform
# Production environment support
resource "bcadmincenter_environment_support_contact" "production" {
  application_family = "BusinessCentral"
  environment_name   = "Production"
  
  name  = "Production Support Team"
  email = "production-support@example.com"
  url   = "https://support.example.com/production"
}

# Sandbox environment support
resource "bcadmincenter_environment_support_contact" "sandbox" {
  application_family = "BusinessCentral"
  environment_name   = "Sandbox"
  
  name  = "Development Support Team"
  email = "dev-support@example.com"
  url   = "https://support.example.com/sandbox"
}
```

